Most of TeaJS docs are available online, see http://code.google.com/p/teajs/wiki/Manual. 
This file is slowly getting obsolete.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

NOTE: replace ~/src with the path where you checkout and build V8 and TeaJS!
NOTE: If you don't like to use vi to edit files, use gedit instead.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

- prerequisites (for compiling all optional components):
sudo apt-get install mysqlclient15-dev libsqlite3-dev libpq-dev libgd2-xpm-dev apache-threaded-dev libxerces-c-dev	## NOTE: if DOM support is not required, then the libxerces-c-dev package can be omitted


- build (replace ~/src with path to where you compile these):
mkdir ~/src
cd ~/src
svn checkout http://v8.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ v8  ## (check for updated instructions at google code: http://code.google.com/p/v8/source/checkout)
hg clone http://code.google.com/p/teajs/ ## (check for updated instructions at google code: http://code.google.com/p/teajs/source/checkout)
chdir v8
scons arch=x64 library=shared
##	OR if not using an x64 OS:
scons library=shared
sudo cp libv8.so /usr/lib/libv8.so
cd ../teajs
scons module=1 gd=1 mysql=1 pgsql=1 sqlite=1 dom=1
sudo cp teajs.conf.posix /etc/teajs.conf


- configure /etc/teajs.conf
sudo vi /etc/teajs.conf
require.paths.push('~/src/teajs/lib');


- configure the apache module:
sudo vi /etc/apache2/mods-available/teajs.load
* The only line in the file should be:
LoadModule teajs_module ~/src/teajs/mod_teajs.so
--
sudo vi /etc/apache2/mods-available/teajs.conf
* The only line in the file should be:
AddHandler teajs-script .sjs .ssjs .jst


- enable the mod:
sudo a2enmod teajs


- create/edit virtual host file
sudo vi /etc/apache2/sites-available/teajs
* This configuration should work, remember to replace ~/src with where you built v8 and TeaJS
----------------------------------------------------------------------
<VirtualHost *:80>
        ServerName teajs
        ServerAdmin webmaster@localhost
        DocumentRoot ~/src/teajs/htdocs

        <Directory ~src/teajs/htdocs>
                Options Indexes All Multiviews
                AllowOverride All
                Order allow,deny
                allow from all
                DirectoryIndex index.sjs
        </Directory>

        ErrorLog /var/log/apache2/teajs_error.log

        # Possible values include: debug, info, notice, warn, error, crit,
        # alert, emerg.
        LogLevel warn

        CustomLog /var/log/apache2/teajs_access.log combined
        ServerSignature On

</VirtualHost>
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

- configure teajs hostname
sudo vi /etc/hosts
* the first line in mine looks like this:
127.0.0.1	localhost teajs

- enable the site
sudo a2ensite teajs

- restart apache:
sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 restart

- Check it out:
point browser at
http://teajs/
